This paper discusses the neurological perspective of individual-intelligence research and expands it to incorporate collective-intelligence within a hyper-cortical construct. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), and Cybernetics (cs.CY).
